<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-10443] findById does not work with ObjectId</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-10443</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using Camel MongoDB component with &quot;operation=findById&quot; and &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;_id&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; field is happened to be a standard ObjectId(), it doesn&apos;t work anymore in v.2.18 (worked 2.17.3 and before). &lt;br/&gt;
Basically, to test you&apos;d need to send org.bson.types.ObjectId in the message body but it never finds a document. &lt;br/&gt;
The problem lies in MongoDbProducer.createDoFindById(). &lt;br/&gt;
Can be fixed by replacing line: &lt;br/&gt;
                String id = exchange1.getIn().getMandatoryBody(String.class); &lt;br/&gt;
with &lt;br/&gt;
                Object id = exchange1.getIn().getMandatoryBody(); &lt;/p&gt;</description>
